4
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:13,110
Welcome to China Uncensored.

5
00:00:13,110 --> 00:00:14,740
I’m your host Chris Chappell.

6
00:00:14,740 --> 00:00:19,380
Okay, I have a message to the tens of thousands
of protesters in Hong Kong

7
00:00:19,380 --> 00:00:22,600
who are upset about Beijing destroying their
freedoms.

8
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,740
You’ve gone too far!

9
00:00:24,740 --> 00:00:28,820
You made poor Hong Kong Chief Executive Carrie
Lam cry.

10
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:33,220
“Some people say I'm betraying Hong Kong.

11
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:35,020
How can I betray Hong Kong?

12
00:00:35,020 --> 00:00:36,940
I was born and raised here.

13
00:00:36,940 --> 00:00:40,480
I was growing up here with all the Hong Kong
people.”

14
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:50,860
That poor woman is just trying her hardest
to make Beijing happy,

15
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:53,000
and you keep asking her to step down.

16
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,620
Have you ever tried walking a mile in her
shoes, huh?

17
00:00:56,620 --> 00:00:59,530
Well, so you know how it feels to cry,

18
00:00:59,530 --> 00:01:03,670
she allowed Hong Kong police to shoot tear
gas at protestors.

19
00:01:03,670 --> 00:01:05,180
And if that doesn’t make you cry,

20
00:01:05,180 --> 00:01:08,510
the pepper spray and rubber bullets will do
the job.

21
00:01:08,510 --> 00:01:12,490
Hong Kong police have been kicking around
some other great ideas, too.

22
00:01:12,490 --> 00:01:15,320
Wow, that’s some good leadership, Carrie
Lam!

23
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:16,690
Don’t feel too bad though,

24
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:20,130
because the Chinese Communist Party’s got
your back.

25
00:01:20,130 --> 00:01:23,680
“China's central government will continue
its firm support

26
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:26,450
for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
government

27
00:01:26,450 --> 00:01:30,890
to push forward with its amendments of the
two extradition bills.”

28
00:01:30,890 --> 00:01:32,450
Those extradition bills are the reason

29
00:01:32,450 --> 00:01:35,430
a million people protested over the weekend.

30
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:36,710
If they get passed,

31
00:01:36,710 --> 00:01:38,560
Chinese authorities could, in some cases,

32
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:40,190
order Hong Kong authorities to arrest

33
00:01:40,190 --> 00:01:43,800
and deport suspected criminals to mainland
China.

34
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:47,280
The Hong Kong Legislature was supposed to
debate the bill on Wednesday.

35
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:50,680
But these pesky protesters got in the way.

36
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:53,440
Look, those barricades are there for a reason!

37
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:57,190
To block off the protest area right outside
the legislature.

38
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:59,440
Well that plan clearly didn’t work.

39
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:00,710
At least 20 people were injured

40
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:03,970
and the extradition bill debate has been delayed.

41
00:02:03,970 --> 00:02:07,670
Carrie Lam is calling the protests organized
riots.

42
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:10,670
And July 1 will be the anniversary of the
1997

43
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:14,130
British handover of Hong Kong to the Chinese
Communist Party.

44
00:02:14,130 --> 00:02:16,050
That’s just a couple weeks away,

45
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:20,130
so it’s possible these protests won’t
be ending anytime soon.

46
00:02:20,130 --> 00:02:24,720
Now, in 2014, police also used tear gas on
protesters,

47
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,200
as well as some hefty violence.

48
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:31,180
That resulted in a months long occupation
of downtown Hong Kong

49
00:02:31,180 --> 00:02:33,680
and international condemnation.

50
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:37,099
So you’d think Hong Kong authorities would
have learned their lesson,

51
00:02:37,099 --> 00:02:42,660
that maybe police brutality is not the way
to deal with these kinds of issues.

52
00:02:42,660 --> 00:02:46,980
Protesters on the other hand have learned
from the 2014 Umbrella Movement.

53
00:02:46,980 --> 00:02:51,040
Back then, they used umbrellas to block police
pepper spray.

54
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:53,349
They’re doing that again this time too.

55
00:02:53,349 --> 00:02:54,349
Just with better branding:

56
00:02:54,349 --> 00:02:57,950
There’s a promo for the new Spider Man:
Far From Home movie!

57
00:02:57,950 --> 00:02:59,280
And for some reason,

58
