75
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:40,690
Christopher Vaiuso asks,

76
00:03:40,690 --> 00:03:42,980
“Why can't the US and other countries

77
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:45,629
just kick China out of the WTO?”

78
00:03:45,629 --> 00:03:46,879
Now that’s a good question.

79
00:03:46,879 --> 00:03:48,830
China has broken so many of its

80
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:51,290
World Trade Organization promises over the
years.

81
00:03:51,290 --> 00:03:53,600
So why not kick China out?

82
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:57,310
Certainly, some in the Trump Administration
have suggested it.

83
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,470
The problem is,

84
00:03:58,470 --> 00:04:01,950
the WTO doesn’t actually have a way to force
a member out.

85
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:05,610
In fact, no country has ever left the WTO,

86
00:04:05,610 --> 00:04:07,500
let alone gotten expelled.

87
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:09,450
But according to the Wall Street Journal,

88
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:12,820
there is an article that can achieve the same
thing.

89
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:16,639
Using Article 23 might allow for amendments
to the WTO charter

90
00:04:16,639 --> 00:04:20,500
that outright prohibits all the things China
is doing,

91
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,270
which would then force China out of the WTO.

92
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:26,710
The problem with that is the WTO usually requires

93
00:04:26,710 --> 00:04:29,069
unanimous votes for doing something.

94
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:31,659
So China could just veto the whole thing.

95
00:04:31,659 --> 00:04:32,849
But if that happens,

96
00:04:32,849 --> 00:04:37,500
it is still possible if there’s a vote by
a supermajority of members.

97
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:42,219
So kicking China out of the WTO would be new
territory.

98
00:04:42,219 --> 00:04:44,240
Possibly China’s sacred territory.

